00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:18,210
♪

51
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:18,480
<i>(crash)</i>

52
00:02:18,515 --> 00:02:19,525
Agh! Wha?

53
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:20,236
Hunh?

54
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:22,232
This is the most complete--

55
00:02:22,347 --> 00:02:23,916
And ginormous!

56
00:02:24,122 --> 00:02:26,001
<i>book on the History</i>
<i>of the Wonderbolts.</i>

57
00:02:26,764 --> 00:02:29,662
OK, but how am I supposed
to get what's in there...

58
00:02:30,042 --> 00:02:31,086
Into here?

59
00:02:31,820 --> 00:02:34,749
With my handy dandy Study
Checklist, of course.

60
00:02:35,299 --> 00:02:36,370
Of course.

61
00:02:37,207 --> 00:02:39,395
First up: Reading
and Highlighting.

62
00:02:40,905 --> 00:02:42,692
Reading and highlighting
is the foundation

63
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,138
of any good study method.

64
00:02:44,524 --> 00:02:46,716
It allows the student to
hone in and boil down

65
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,982
what's really important,

66
00:02:48,216 --> 00:02:49,990
separating the
good from the bad,

67
00:02:50,056 --> 00:02:52,909
<i>the wheat from the chaff,</i>
<i>getting to the crux of things.</i>

68
00:02:53,445 --> 00:02:55,059
Let's see what
you've got so far.

69
00:02:55,285 --> 00:02:56,349
Um...

70
00:02:56,878 --> 00:02:57,426
Huh?

71
00:02:58,111 --> 00:03:00,540
By highlighting everything,
you don't really

72
00:03:00,552 --> 00:03:03,422
separate the wheat
from the chaff.

73
00:03:04,776 --> 00:03:06,774
Or the good from the bad.

74
00:03:07,957 --> 00:03:10,113
Hey. I am not that tall!

75
00:03:10,961 --> 00:03:12,109
<i>(chuckle)</i>

76
00:03:15,061 --> 00:03:16,240
(sigh) OK, Rainbow.

77
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:19,182
Clearly reading and highlighting
is not your style of studying.

78
00:03:19,479 --> 00:03:21,660
<i>So let's move on to</i>
<i>the tried and true.</i>

79
00:03:22,614 --> 00:03:23,631
History Lecture!

80
00:03:26,632 --> 00:03:27,537
Yes, Rainbow?

81
00:03:28,485 --> 00:03:29,910
Is it snack time?

82
00:03:30,446 --> 00:03:30,850
No.

83
00:03:31,385 --> 00:03:32,419
Recess?

84
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,036
No.

85
00:03:34,146 --> 00:03:36,702
Can't we just watch the History
of the Wonderbolts movie?

86
00:03:37,285 --> 00:03:38,080
No!

87
00:03:38,485 --> 00:03:40,930
Now just get comfortable
and experience...

88
00:03:41,994 --> 00:03:43,886
the magic of learning.

89
00:03:45,215 --> 00:03:46,095
Ahem!

90
00:03:46,427 --> 00:03:48,520
Prior to the great
Celestia/Luna Rift,

91
00:03:48,803 --> 00:03:51,754
there was no need for the
Earth, Unicorn, Pegasi,

92
00:03:52,056 --> 00:03:53,672
or E.U.P.--Guard.

93
00:03:54,044 --> 00:03:54,643
<i>(sigh)</i>

94
00:03:54,751 --> 00:03:56,460
<i>But after Luna's banishment,</i>

95
00:03:56,595 --> 00:03:58,899
<i>the Protective Pony</i>
<i>Platoons</i> were formed.

96
00:03:59,818 --> 00:04:02,444
<i>On the anniversary of the</i>
<i>first Celestial Year of Peace,</i>

97
00:04:02,684 --> 00:04:04,308
a celebration was held.

98
00:04:04,897 --> 00:04:06,729
<i>♪ (imitate military band) </i>

99
00:04:06,794 --> 00:04:08,376
Headed by General Firefly...

100
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:10,965
<i>An elite team of aerial</i>
<i>performers were chosen</i>

101
00:04:10,979 --> 00:04:13,309
<i>to help commemorate this</i>
<i>auspicious occasion.</i>

102
00:04:13,918 --> 00:04:16,251
The first performance
was so full of energy,

103
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:19,845
so highly charged, that magical
lightning showered down

104
00:04:19,851 --> 00:04:20,606
on the crowd.

105
00:04:20,856 --> 00:04:23,381
<i>Everypony was so filled</i>
<i>with amazement and wonder</i>

106
00:04:23,598 --> 00:04:27,239
that General Firefly dubbed
them the Wonderbolts.

107
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:32,829
Rainbow Dash!

108
00:04:33,002 --> 00:04:35,069
Can you repeat
any of my lesson?

109
00:04:37,656 --> 00:04:38,538
<i>(poof!)</i>

110
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:39,929
<i>(crash)</i>

111
00:04:42,858 --> 00:04:43,824
<i>(horn honk)</i>

112
00:04:46,464 --> 00:04:47,014
<i>(chuckle)</i>

113
00:04:47,032 --> 00:04:48,497
<i>(giggle)</i>

114
00:04:55,943 --> 00:04:57,139
History lecture?

115
00:04:57,689 --> 00:04:59,264
Nope. (sigh)

116
00:04:59,369 --> 00:05:02,240
OK, Rainbow...Rainbow?

117
00:05:02,864 --> 00:05:03,797
Rainbow Dash!

118
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:04,329
<i>(whoosh)</i>

119
00:05:04,757 --> 00:05:05,235
Here.

120
00:05:06,255 --> 00:05:11,334
Let's move on to my favorite
style of learning: Flashcards.

121
00:05:12,692 --> 00:05:16,647
Ooh! Does that mean
I'll learn in a flash?

122
00:05:17,465 --> 00:05:18,788
One can only hope.

123
00:05:20,942 --> 00:05:23,654
Colonel Purple Dart, the leader
of the Wonderbolts in the

124
00:05:23,736 --> 00:05:25,473
4th Celestial Era was
known for his...

125
00:05:25,498 --> 00:05:25,875
<i>(splat)</i>

126
00:05:26,107 --> 00:05:26,762
Wha?

127
00:05:27,469 --> 00:05:29,438
Rainbow, did you
see what happened?

128
00:05:29,890 --> 00:05:34,267
What? No! I was riveted by
your captivating cards.

129
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:36,005
Hmmmm.

130
00:05:36,829 --> 00:05:39,008
After becoming the
official flying squadron

131
00:05:39,014 --> 00:05:41,465
for Princess Celestia, she
honored them with...

132
00:05:42,031 --> 00:05:42,813
Gotcha!

133
00:05:43,371 --> 00:05:43,982
Got what?

134
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:49,047
The original Wonderbolts
lightning bolt insignia was...

135
00:05:49,324 --> 00:05:50,080
Ah!

136
00:05:51,221 --> 00:05:52,160
Rainbow Dash.

137
00:05:52,173 --> 00:05:53,332
You could have hurt me.

138
00:05:54,177 --> 00:05:56,282
With a spit wad? Really?

139
00:05:56,569 --> 00:05:59,127
A spit wad to the eye would
have been no laughing matter.

140
00:06:01,582 --> 00:06:03,209
Well, if you can horse
around like this,

141
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:05,469
then you clearly must
be ready for the test.

142
00:06:06,081 --> 00:06:06,675
Clearly!

143
00:06:07,278 --> 00:06:09,756
Well then, I guess you're
also ready for a...

144
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,147
(poof poof!)

145
00:06:11,410 --> 00:06:12,667
pop quiz.

146
00:06:12,885 --> 00:06:13,691
Bring it!

147
00:06:14,441 --> 00:06:15,640
(poof poof!)

148
00:06:15,797 --> 00:06:18,503
The initials E.U.P.
stand for what?

149
00:06:18,975 --> 00:06:20,665
Ernie's Undercooked Pancakes.

150
00:06:20,856 --> 00:06:23,149
The original aerial
team performed for...

151
00:06:23,307 --> 00:06:25,121
Celestia's Cereal
Celebration.

152
00:06:25,914 --> 00:06:29,096
The Wonderbolts were given their
name by this famous Pegasus.

153
00:06:29,414 --> 00:06:30,279
Who is she?

154
00:06:30,831 --> 00:06:32,169
Please don't say Colonel Waffle.

155
00:06:32,710 --> 00:06:35,929
Hello? General
Blazing Donut Glaze.

156
00:06:36,003 --> 00:06:36,558
<i>(scoff)</i>

157
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:40,550
So, did I ace it or what?

158
00:06:40,911 --> 00:06:42,120
Or what.

159
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,534
You didn't get one
answer correct.

160
00:06:44,801 --> 00:06:46,362
What? But how?

161
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,471
I don't know.

162
00:06:47,578 --> 00:06:49,116
I've never heard
answers so wrong.

163
00:06:49,603 --> 00:06:51,127
And so breakfast related.

164
00:06:51,221 --> 00:06:52,803
<i>(stomach growling)</i>

165
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,205
If you had taken the
official test today...

166
00:06:55,652 --> 00:06:58,120
(gasp) My dreams of being
in the Wonderbolts Reserves

167
00:06:58,132 --> 00:07:00,025
would've been totally crushed.

168
00:07:01,094 --> 00:07:02,282
What am I gonna do?

169
00:07:02,456 --> 00:07:03,789
I'm running out of time!

170
00:07:03,861 --> 00:07:05,385
I don't know any
of this history!

171
00:07:05,945 --> 00:07:08,487
I'm going to fail!

172
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:12,697
♪

173
00:07:12,796 --> 00:07:15,912
I'm gonna fail, I'm gonna
fail, I'm gonna fail.

174
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,140
And it's all your fault!

175
00:07:18,259 --> 00:07:19,186
My fault?

176
00:07:19,498 --> 00:07:21,000
I'm the one helping you.

177
00:07:21,656 --> 00:07:23,082
Maybe your famous
"study methods"

178
00:07:23,092 --> 00:07:24,450
aren't all they're
cracked up to be!

179
00:07:24,587 --> 00:07:25,730
Eh, teacher?

180
00:07:26,903 --> 00:07:29,931
Excuse me, I've used them
to study for many a test

181
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:31,094
and passed.

182
00:07:31,447 --> 00:07:32,801
Yeah, right.

183
00:07:33,051 --> 00:07:35,773
Do you know the name of the
premiere Wonderbolts choreographer?

184
00:07:36,263 --> 00:07:37,535
Uh, well...

185
00:07:37,894 --> 00:07:39,566
Commander Easy Glider.

186
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:42,575
Do you know how many Pegasi
flew in the original squad?

187
00:07:43,098 --> 00:07:43,615
Um...

188
00:07:43,873 --> 00:07:44,452
Seven!

189
00:07:44,776 --> 00:07:47,715
Do you know Princess Celestia's
favorite flight pattern?

190
00:07:48,183 --> 00:07:50,569
The Icaranian Sun Salutation.

191
00:07:50,794 --> 00:07:53,143
See? I could
pass the test.

192
00:07:53,658 --> 00:07:54,158
Fine.

193
00:07:54,323 --> 00:07:55,555
Rub it in, why
don't you?

194
00:07:55,797 --> 00:07:59,293
Besides, I don't see why I have
to take this lousy test anyway.

195
00:07:59,547 --> 00:08:02,080
I've proven I'm one of
the best fliers around.

196
00:08:02,308 --> 00:08:05,071
Knowing their origin and being
able to properly represent them

197
00:08:05,084 --> 00:08:07,765
for all of Equestria
is just as important.

198
00:08:08,019 --> 00:08:08,989
Yeah, right.

199
00:08:09,178 --> 00:08:11,471
<i>Some history buff like you</i>
<i>must've made that up</i>

200
00:08:11,484 --> 00:08:13,065
to bring us fliers down.

201
00:08:13,305 --> 00:08:16,130
Knowing history actually
is beneficial, Rainbow.

202
00:08:16,216 --> 00:08:17,295
(raspberry)

203
00:08:17,352 --> 00:08:19,141
Beneficial for eggheads.

204
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:19,912
Girls.

205
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:22,954
Well, this egghead knows
history and can fly.

206
00:08:23,254 --> 00:08:25,057
Maybe I should
become a Wonderbolt.

207
00:08:25,141 --> 00:08:27,701
Just 'cause you've got wings
doesn't mean you can fly.

208
00:08:27,777 --> 00:08:28,489
Girls!

209
00:08:28,579 --> 00:08:30,759
You're barely able to
just get off the ground.

210
00:08:30,815 --> 00:08:31,625
<i>(horrified gasp)</i>

211
00:08:31,710 --> 00:08:32,400
<i>(growl)</i>

212
00:08:32,433 --> 00:08:34,249
Girls! Stop!

213
00:08:36,288 --> 00:08:38,823
Now, is that any way
to talk to a friend?

214
00:08:41,274 --> 00:08:42,005
Sorry.

215
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:44,226
Yeah, sorry.

216
00:08:44,796 --> 00:08:46,641
Don't you have more
important things to do?

217
00:08:46,831 --> 00:08:49,139
Like prepare Rainbow
for her big test?

218
00:08:49,719 --> 00:08:51,223
I've tried everything,
Fluttershy,

219
00:08:51,457 --> 00:08:53,508
but none of my study
methods work for her.

220
00:08:54,119 --> 00:08:56,704
Well, no offense to your
teaching methods, Twilight,

221
00:08:56,837 --> 00:08:58,926
but I think I may have
a way to help Rainbow.

222
00:09:03,047 --> 00:09:04,497
Oh! Who's that?
Who's that?

223
00:09:04,883 --> 00:09:07,734
Celestia and Luna, back
when they were happy.

224
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:13,916
<i>♪ (piano) </i>

225
00:09:13,921 --> 00:09:14,920
<i>(yowl)</i>

226
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:28,733
♪

227
00:09:29,363 --> 00:09:30,199
Now what?

228
00:09:30,526 --> 00:09:35,106
Gummy's an Earth Pony; Winona's
a Unicorn and Tank is a Pegasus.

229
00:09:35,455 --> 00:09:36,476
They're the E.U.P.

230
00:09:36,563 --> 00:09:38,183
helping to protect
the Princess.

231
00:09:42,021 --> 00:09:43,531
How are you
getting all this?

232
00:09:51,278 --> 00:09:51,923
<i>(crash)</i>

233
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:53,137
Oh no!

234
00:09:54,581 --> 00:09:55,348
<i>(smash)</i>

235
00:09:56,829 --> 00:09:57,829
<i>(thud)</i>

236
00:09:57,831 --> 00:09:58,930
<i>(rumble)</i>

237
00:09:58,948 --> 00:10:00,222
Stop, stop, stop!

238
00:10:00,452 --> 00:10:01,157
That was aw--

239
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,048
Awesome!

240
00:10:02,142 --> 00:10:04,977
I give it three "Woo hoos"
Woo hoo, Woo hoo, Woo hoo!

241
00:10:05,112 --> 00:10:06,690
And an extra "Woo"
for good measure.

242
00:10:06,835 --> 00:10:07,601
Woo!

